   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>THE BELIEVERS' LIVING FOR THE BUILDING UP</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>OF THE ORGANIC BODY OF CHRIST The Basic Principles</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>In order to live such a life, there are a number of principles and details that we need to pay attention to.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Not Walking as the Nations Walk,</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>in the Vanity of Their Mind</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The first principle is that we should not walk as the nations walk, in the vanity of their mind v. 17 . Everyone in the world, both young and old, male and female, lingers in his or her mind.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Even while they are sleeping, they remain in their mind.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>This is why so many people have dreams.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>If someone thinks about having a big house or a good car, he will dream about these things at night.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>This is to walk in the vanity of the mind.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Whatever is in the mind is vanity.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The wise King Solomon said that everything under the sun is vanity of vanities Eccl.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>1:2 .</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>As a saved person, we should never walk in the vanity of the mind.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Not Being Estranged from the Life of God,</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Which Is for the Divine Dispensing</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The second principle is that we should not be estranged from the life of God Eph 4:18 .</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>We the believers have the life of God within us.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>But even we are quite often estranged from the life of God.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>We do not keep ourselves linked, connected, and joined to the divine life.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>We do have this life, but we do not use it or depend on it.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Instead, we put it aside.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>It is a serious thing to be estranged from the life of God.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Electricity may be installed in a building, but if even a thin piece of paper is inserted between the wires, the electricity will be stopped.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>It is easy to stop the electrical current.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>If we stop the electrical current, electricity will still be here, but there will be no way to apply it to us.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>In such a case, we will be estranged from electricity.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>It is the same with the life of God.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Although we have the life of God, we can easily be estranged from it.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Not Ceasing from Caring for</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>the Feeling of Their Conscience</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>The third principle is that we must not cease from caring for the feeling of the conscience v. 19 . Our conscience must be very keen.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>It must be in a good condition.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>Whenever we sense condemnation in our conscience, we need to take care of it immediately Acts 24:16 .</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>It is a dangerous thing to ignore the conscience.</S>
   </TEXT>
